article.description: Jared Mintz scored six points in the final 35 seconds to lift Lafayette past Holy Cross 66-63 on Sunday in a Patriot League Conference tournament semifinal.
article.shortLinkText: Mintz helps Lafayette edge upstart Holy Cross
article.headline: Mintz's late surge helps Lafayette end Holy Cross' surprising run
article.linkText: Holy Cross edged out in Patriot League semis
article.story: EASTON, Pa. -- Jared Mintz scored six points in the final 35 seconds to lift Lafayette past Holy Cross 66-63 on Sunday in a Patriot League Conference tournament semifinal. The Leopards (19-12) were up 39-30 at halftime, led by 12 of Jim Mower's 17 points -- all on 3s -- but the lead changed hands eight times in the second half. Mike Cavataio's tip-in put the Crusaders (10-21) up 63-62 with 56 seconds to play. Mintz then hit a jumper on Lafayette's next possession, and after Holy Cross missed a field goal, Mintz made two free throws with 6 seconds left for the final margin. The Leopards, who improved to 6-0 in conference tournament games at home, will play the winner of the Lehigh-American game on Friday. Mower went 5-for-10 from 3-point range and Jeff Kari added 10 for third-seeded Lafayette. RJ Evans led the seventh-seeded Crusaders with 21 points.
